title: China tests engines for moon mission rocket
summary: China has conducted a series of successful hot fire tests for engines designed to power a launch vehicle capable of sending astronauts to the moon.

title: SpaceX still an option for future Amazon internet satellite launches, says Senior VP
summary: An Amazon executive says that the company could still call on SpaceX to launch some of its Project Kuiper internet satellites after...

title: Lunar landing restored for Artemis 4 mission
summary: NASA has restored plans to include a lunar landing on its Artemis 4 mission to the moon later this decade, months after saying that the mission would instead be devoted to assembly of the lunar Gateway.

title: China launches Mengtian science module to Tiangong space station
summary: China launched its second space station module of the year aboard a Chang Zheng 5B rocket Monday. The Mengtian module lifted off at 07:37 UTC, and once docked will complete the initial phase of the construction for China’s Tiangong space station.

title: First NorthStar SSA satellites to launch in 2023 by Virgin Orbit
summary: NorthStar Earth and Space, a company planning a constellation of satellites to collect space situational awareness data, will launch its first satellites in mid-2023 with Virgin Orbit.

title: For U.S. Space Force, Raymond’s retirement marks the end of an era
summary: The first chief of space operations Gen. John 'Jay' Raymond  retires Nov. 2 after 38 years of military service

title: Centaur issue delays JPSS-2 launch
summary: The launch of a polar-orbiting weather satellite and reentry technology demonstration will be delayed more than a week because of a battery problem with the upper stage of their rocket, NASA announced Oct. 29.

title: Psyche launch rescheduled for October 2023
summary: A NASA mission to an asteroid that missed its launch window this fall because of technical issues has been rescheduled for launch next October.

title: Constellation antenna provider SatixFy goes public after SPAC merger
summary: Satcoms equipment maker SatixFy started trading publicly Oct. 28 after its stock listing overcame waning investor interest in blank check mergers and the death of its co-founder and former CEO.

title: NASA to Provide Update on Artemis I Moon Mission
summary: NASA will host a media teleconference at 12 p.m. EDT Thursday, Nov. 3, to discuss the status of its Artemis I flight test that will launch the Space Launch System (SLS) rocket from NASA’s Kennedy Space Center in Florida. The uncrewed mission will send the Orion spacecraft beyond the Moon and back to Earth before future missions with crew.
